 examines the meanings, boundaries, opportunities, and limits of commemoration, a phenomenon not unique to Israel but shared by many nations across the globe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMemorializationzIsrael. 0aMemoryxSocial aspectszIsrael. 0aPublic opinionzIsrael. 4aArea Studies : Israel Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781438428390?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438428390423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438428390/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles